snippet.title: Not Almost There
snippet.description:
If the 19-year old Joe Chura saw what I have accomplished, he would think I had “made it”. Working on the assembly line at Ford’s Chicago Assembly Plant, studying textbooks 8 seconds at a time between vehicles to get a degree — his life goal was to get promoted off the line, maybe to the marketing department.

Since then I’ve founded and sold two of the fastest growing companies in America, transformed my life and health, and focused on giving back — and I would tell 19-year old Joe that I’m just getting started.

Many have inspired and taught me along the way, and so it’s become my passion to pay those lessons forward to help others achieve more than they ever thought they could.
